  "text": "35 S] in vitro cell labeling mix (GE Healthcare, Chalfont St. Giles, UK) in cysteine/methionine-free Dulbecco's modified Eagle's medium. After homogenization of cells in hypotonic lysis buffer (10 mM Tris, 1 mM EDTA, 0.2% Triton X-100), labeled proteins were precipitated with 10% trichloroacetic acid, resuspended in 0.2 N NaOH, and measured by liquid scintillation counting. Evaluation of cell viability was based on the incorporation of the supravital dye neutral red by viable cells [CITATION_1] .",
